<tt>Sat Nov 30 23:27:07 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
Mr. Parson - to compare the American soldier to unthinking cattle is unthinking and malicious.  As a marine combat vet of Vietnam, I am more than willing to acknowledge the courage it took to stand against national policies Vietnam protestors thought were wrong.  Now, are you willing to acknowledge the courage it took to stand with our Vietnamese brothers and sisters against what we sincerely believed was aggression?  I didn't volunteer blindly - I truly believed the South Vietnamese needed our help.<br><br>
I admit that I was wrong - but I had to go over there to find out for sure.  Are you, and others like you, willing to admit that you were (and are) wrong to denigrate our sincere efforts?
<p><code>-- miketol@mtco.com  (Mike Toliver) </code><p>


